{"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Instance Property","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"sliceHeight","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"UltraliteSDK"}],"externalID":"s:12UltraliteSDK12ScrollLayoutC12AutoScrollerC11sliceHeightSiSgvp","title":"sliceHeight","symbolKind":"property"},"abstract":[{"text":"Calculated height of each slice","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller\/sliceHeight","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"sliceHeight"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"! { get }"}]}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout\/autoscroller\/sliceheight"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK","doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout","doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller"]]},"references":{"doc://UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK/ScrollLayout/AutoScroller":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"AutoScroller","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller","title":"ScrollLayout.AutoScroller","url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout\/autoscroller","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"AutoScroller"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"AutoScroller is a utility class to send a large known block of predfined text to the glasses to be smoothly scrolled."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"This is simlar to what is seen on a teleprompter or in movie credits.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"This class was written using the "},{"code":"ScrollLayout","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" commands and is nothing more than a convience class.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Everything used this class can be written from the public SDK.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It scrolls the text much like a teleprompter would with basic commands to pause and resume the scrolling.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The duration (speed) of the scrolling can be modified while scrolling by seting the "},{"code":"duration","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" property."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It can support any language that the font supports.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If the content is not known up front, or subject to change, this is the utility class will not work (use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"LiveText"},{"text":" instance instead).","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK/ScrollLayout/AutoScroller/sliceHeight":{"abstract":[{"text":"Calculated height of each slice","type":"text"}],"title":"sliceHeight","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"sliceHeight","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller\/sliceHeight","role":"symbol","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout\/autoscroller\/sliceheight"},"doc://UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK":{"type":"topic","title":"UltraliteSDK","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this SDK to easily send text and images to your Vuxix smart glasses."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK","url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk","role":"collection"},"doc://UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK/ScrollLayout":{"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ScrollLayout","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout","identifier":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout","abstract":[{"text":"When Ultralite.requestControl with a .scroll layout type .. this is the class you interate with to draw scrolling text to the screen.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Once the layout is .scrolled you must send one configure message to tell the layout how to setup.  It will setup the slice height and how many slices are visible."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"There are two supported modes: autoScroll on\/off"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"When autoScroll is true, the slices are automatically scrolled.  Subscribe to the delgate and listen for the scrolled callback, when you get it send another slice of text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"When autoScroll is false, you can drive the slices and how they look on the screen.  You can send all the slices at once or send one at a time and animate it onto the screen at the current time.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","title":"ScrollLayout","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ScrollLayout","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic"}}}